```

- VSCode Version: 0.10.11
- OS Version: OS X 10.11.3

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Write a JS function like this:

```
   .run(function (Config) {
    // some code here
    });
```
1. press alt+shift+f
2. Result:

```
 .run(function(Config) {
    // some code here
  });

```
1. The whitespace between `function` and `(Config)` part gets deleted, which leads to our linter crying!
2. Expected result:

```
 .run(function (Config) {
    // some code here
  });

```

Bug.

- VSCode Version: 0.10.11
- OS Version: Mac OS X 10.10.5

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Create a new javascript file and add this source

```
import React from 'react';

export default class Item extends React.Component {
    update(e) {
        console.log(e.target.value);
    }

    test = (e) => {
        console.log(e.target.value);
    }

    render() {
        return <span>{this.props.name}<br/>
<input type="text" onChange={(e) => this.update(e)} /><br/>
<input type="text" onChange={this.test} />
</span>;
    }
}
```
